result.name: Hoi Fu Restaurant

reviews.text: Nice hardworking people nice Place to have lunch!

Close by to where I'm currently staying - the dinner specials are great! Everything is in Chinese so you better bring someone who can read chinese. We got the steamed fish and it was really good size- even the server walked by and was like "omg". ( a different server) Also had the bowl of fish and fried tofu which was very good and a plate of greens. You get two soups with this dinner set but since it was the last of the soup- the bus boy got us 3- one for each of us which was very nice :) You also get two bowls of white rice and the server asked if we wanted another bowl so I can get some rice from each of the bowls which was thoughtful. Will probably frequent this place a lot since it's convenient. Very clean and spacious, love the booths. You also get tea when you sit down.
Local eatery. Prices are ok.
A local restaurant providing good food at a reasonable price. Not for tourists though.
So far so good
